    <modellingAndValidation>
      <representativeness systemModelId="290c1f85-4cc4-4fa1-b0c8-2cb7f4276dce">
        <systemModelName xml:lang="en">Allocation, cut-off by classification</systemModelName>
        <samplingProcedure xml:lang="en">Data collection has been performed by the Alliance for European Flax-Linen &amp; Hemp from referent sources incl. Arvalis and Inagro (agronomic institutes referent respectively for France and for Belgium-Netherlands) for average agricultural technical itinerary practiced in these 3 countries; and interbranch production statistics. These data represent the European production which is 100% certified to European Flax (TM) and amounts for 3/4 of the global production for fibre, flax, long, scutched on 2023.</samplingProcedure>
        <extrapolations xml:lang="en">The data on inputs to the field activities are collected directly from the Alliance for European Flax-Linen &amp; Hemp. The ecoinvent LCI calculation tool for crop production was used to calculate field emissions from the cultivation process.</extrapolations>
      </representativeness>
